TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,5);
$b = random(1,4);

$P = "(x**2+$a**2)*(x-$b)**2";

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
A degree 4 polynomial \(P(x)\) with integer coefficients has zeros \( $a i \) and $b,
with $b being a zero of multiplicity 2. Moreover, the coefficient of \(x^4\) is 1.
Find the polynomial.
 
$BR
\( P(x) = \)  \{ans_rule(35)\}
    
$BR   
EOT



&ANS(fun_cmp($P));



